                <h2>How to cancel a British Airways Flight</h2>
                <p class="text-justify">In order to cancel your British Airways flight, the first place you need to visit is the 'Manage My Booking' portal on the British Airways website. </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>Here you must provide the lead passenger's name and you’re booking reference. You will find this on your confirmation email or e-ticket. </li>
                    <li>You are going to find the options available that are necessary for amending or cancelling your booking and whether any fees will apply. </li>
                    <li>You can also call British Airways customer services if you have any doubts or questions regarding cancelling or amending a flight. If so, keep your booking reference ready and call 0344 493 0787. The customer service number is available between 6 am and 8 pm daily. </li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Cancellation Policy- British Airways</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">One can <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/british-airways-cancellation-policy.aspx">cancel British Airways flight online</a> without facing any hassles. Passengers are also eligible to request a refund online. For this, they must fill out the refund request form at British Airways' official site. The airline only provides refunds for eligible British Airways flight tickets cancelled within the active period. You must note that airways only provide a refund after the expiry period of the ticket. </p>

                <p class="text-justify">The British Airways refund request might take some time to be processed. Generally, the refund gets processed within 7 to 10 working days. In case the flights are cancelled due to unavoidable reasons from the British Airways end. The airline will provide compensation to the passengers through which they can book the subsequent British Airways flight. Hence you can cancel your flight and get a refund from British Airways. </p>

                <h3>British Airways cancellation fees</h3>
                <p class="text-justify">British Airways have prescribed a cancellation fee for both domestic and international flights. In case you are not familiar with the <strong>British Airways flight cancellation fee</strong> for international flights, then you must go through the below instructions: </p>

                <ul>
                    <li>	You need to pay a cancellation fee of $100 to $500 only if you request the cancellation of the fee after 24 hours as a risk-free cancellation.</li>
                    <li>	A fee of $100 to $400 will be charged as a British Airways cancellation fee in case you cancel your British Airways flight within 24 hours of your flight's scheduled departure. </li>
                    <li>	After you have cancelled your flight ticket, you can also make a cancellation request. </li>
                </ul>

                <p class="text-justify">This is all the information regarding <strong>British Airways Cancellation Policy</strong>. It is straightforward on the part of travellers. By booking flights in advance, you can get hold of <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/cheap-flights.aspx">cheap tickets on British Airways</a>. You are always free to contact the customer service centre in case of queries. </p>



