                <h5 class="text-justify">How to cancel a flight ticket with British Airways? </h5>
                <p class="text-justify">You can call the British Airways customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. Also, you can visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
                <h5 class="text-justify">How can I make the request for a refund? By when can I expect it? </h5>
                <p class="text-justify">You can visit the official website of British Airways and make a request for a refund or you can call customer care. It takes time to process the refunds; hence, you may receive refunds within 7 to 20 business days. </p>
                <h5 class="text-justify">Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h5>
                <p class="text-justify">There can be a possibility that your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
